President Obama has nominated Judge Richard Franklin Boulware II and Judge Charles R. Breyer to serve on the United States Sentencing Commission. Both judges have extensive legal backgrounds and are known for their commitment to justice. Judge Boulware has been a United States District Judge for the District of Nevada since 2014 and has previously worked at the Federal Public Defender's Office in Las Vegas. Judge Breyer has been a United States District Judge in the Northern District of California since 1998 and has worked at a law firm and as an Assistant District Attorney prior to that. Both judges have impressive educational backgrounds, with Judge Boulware receiving his J.D. from Columbia Law School and Judge Breyer receiving his J.D. from the University of California at Berkeley Boalt Hall School of Law.